🏦 Bank Loan Analysis | SQL + Power BI
This project analyzes bank loan performance data using MS SQL Server and visualizes insights through a professional Power BI dashboard. It demonstrates end-to-end data handling—from raw ingestion to interactive reporting.

📌 Objective
To help stakeholders understand key loan trends, monitor good vs. bad loan performance, and make data-driven lending decisions.

🛠 Tools & Technologies

MySQL
MySQL Workbench
Power BI (June 2025 version)
Excel 2021

🔍 Key Features
🔹 SQL Analysis
Created database & tables
Wrote queries to calculate:
Total Applications, Funded Amount, Amount Received
Good vs Bad Loans
Avg. Interest Rate, Avg. Debt-to-Income Ratio
Used CTEs, date functions, group by, and case logic

🔹 Power BI Dashboards
📊 Dashboard 1: Summary
KPIs with MTD & MoM trends
Good vs Bad Loan segmentation
Loan status grid view

🌐 Dashboard 2: Overview
Monthly loan trends
Regional analysis (Map)
Term, employment, purpose, and home ownership breakdowns

📋 Dashboard 3: Details
Comprehensive grid for deep dives
Borrower-level insights

🧠 Skills Demonstrated
Data modeling (fact/dimension structure)
Power Query transformations
DAX (Time intelligence, KPIs)
Dashboard design & UX best practices
Business-oriented storytelling


